!!!
! compile with gfortran-5 or gfortran-6 (not >=7!)
! otherwise strength (or broadening?)
! of heavy metal lines will be wrong (too weak)!
! maybe only for lines that don't have GammaStark provided?
! only Z>30 affected -> maybe something in that subroutine?
! some Sr, YIII, Zr, Sn, Pb lines def. affected, both in UV and optical.
! effect is worse in UV!
!!!

module load gcc/5.5.0 
gfortran -fno-automatic -O3 -Wall -o binary/synspec51_v3_HeI_addantoine_final_addNb_pscont_gf5 synspec51_v3_HeI_addantoine_final_addNb_pscont.f
# add libgfortran.so.4 path to the binary itself, such that it is found also when the module gcc/5.5.0 is not loaded
gfortran -fno-automatic -O3 -Wall -Wl,--rpath=/software/Ubuntu-20.04/Programming/gcc/5.5.0/lib64 -Wl,--disable-new-dtags -o binary/synspec51_v3_HeI_addantoine_final_addNb_pscont_gf5 synspec51_v3_HeI_addantoine_final_addNb_pscont.f
# if gfortran-6 is available
gfortran-6 -fno-automatic -fno-align-commons -O3 -Wall -o synspec51_fork synspec51_fork.f

